# Lessons Tracker — Project Rules

## Tech Stack
- Next.js 15 (App Router)
- React 19
- MUI v6 (Material UI) — dark theme only
- Redux Toolkit + RTK Query (with optimistic updates)
- TanStack React Table v8
- Prisma + SQLite
- FullCalendar for calendar views
- TypeScript strict mode

## Architecture: Feature-Sliced Design (FSD)
```
src/
  app/        — Next.js App Router, layout, providers, theme
  widgets/    — composite UI blocks (calendar, tables, sidebar)
  features/   — user-facing interactions (create lesson, create student, etc.)
  entities/   — business entities (student, lesson) with RTK Query API slices
  shared/     — shared utilities, base API, constants, UI primitives
```

### Import rules
- shared → no upper layer imports
- entities → shared only
- features → entities, shared
- widgets → features, entities, shared
- app → all layers

## Naming Conventions
- Files: camelCase (e.g., `lessonCalendar.tsx`, `studentApi.ts`)
- Components: PascalCase exports
- Types/Interfaces: PascalCase with descriptive names
- API routes: kebab-case folders (Next.js convention)

## Language
- UI text: Ukrainian
- Code (variables, functions, types): English
- No comments in code

## Database
- Prisma with SQLite (file-based, persistent)
- Schema in `prisma/schema.prisma`

## Key Business Rules
- Individual lesson price: 200 UAH
- Group lesson price: 50 UAH per student
- Lesson statuses: PLANNED, COMPLETED, MISSED, CANCELLED
- COMPLETED and MISSED — charge the student
- CANCELLED — no charge
- Payment tracking per student per lesson
